# Journey-phase operating protocol

**SSOT:** [docs/architecture/journey-phase-playbook.md](docs/architecture/journey-phase-playbook.md)

Before writing any product code, run this seven-step gate:

---

## Step 1 â€” Name the phase

Pick exactly one:

| Phase ID              | Canonical routes                                                                           |
| --------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| `pre-login`           | `/` `/auth/*` `/org/login` `/client/login` `/invite/[token]` `/f/[token]` `/survey/[slug]` |
| `join`                | `/join?invitationId=`                                                                      |
| `onboarding`          | `/client/onboarding`                                                                       |
| `client-post-login`   | `/client` `/client/profile` `/client/declare/[id]`                                         |
| `operator-post-login` | `/dashboard` `/dashboard/clients` `/dashboard/[id]`                                        |
| `hot-sales`           | `/trade/*` â€” **stop and confirm gate-register before touching**                            |

If the task spans more than one phase, stop and ask the user which one to take first.

---

## Step 2 â€” Run preflight

Confirm every item in the phase's preflight checklist in [docs/architecture/journey-phase-playbook.md](docs/architecture/journey-phase-playbook.md#c-preflight-checklist).

For `operator-post-login`, also run [docs/architecture/admincn-frontend-preflight.md](docs/architecture/admincn-frontend-preflight.md).

---

## Step 3 â€” Check three perspectives (`fullstack-guardian`)

Before writing a single file, confirm these three layers are covered:

**Frontend**
Route â†’ `lib/entry/*` or `lib/pages/*` â†’ `features/` or `portal-views/` â†’ `loading.tsx` present

**Backend**
`app/actions/*.ts` â†’ Zod schema in `lib/schemas/` â†’ `requireSession` guard â†’ `lib/domain/*.ts` â†’ Neon

**Security**
`proxy.ts` matcher/bypass correct Â· session guard at layout Â· `sanitizeReturnToPath` on any `returnTo` Â· parameterized queries only in `lib/domain/`

---

## Step 4 â€” Auto-enrich

Before implementing, scan for gaps and fill them in the same pass:

- UI page without a server action â†’ add action + Zod schema
- Server action without UI â†’ add feature component + page delegation
- Action without `lib/domain/` function â†’ add domain function
- Doc references deleted file â†’ update doc
- `loading.tsx` missing on route â†’ add skeleton file
- Governance registry out of sync â†’ run `npm run export:reliance-mapping`

**Never commit a half-stack slice.**

---

## Step 5 â€” One phase only

Do not pull in adjacent phases, Hot Sales 2Bâ€“2D, portal atmosphere experiments, or the client-workspace rebuild unless the user explicitly reopens scope in this turn.

---

## Step 6 â€” Implement once

After preflight, implement the full vertical slice in one pass. Do not write partial stubs expecting a follow-up turn.

---

## Step 7 â€” Verify or replan

Run phase verify commands from the playbook. On any failure:
1. Stop immediately
2. State the exact command output and error
3. Propose a concrete replan

**Do not enter an open-ended debug exploration loop.**

---

## Definition of Done (applies to every phase)

| Perspective     | Pass criteria                                                                                                                              |
| --------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| **Frontend**    | Route delegates to entry/page runner; feature component mounts; `loading.tsx` present; no inline business logic in `app/` page file        |
| **Backend**     | Zod-validated input; `requireSession` guard; domain-only DB access; no raw SQL in action layer                                             |
| **Security**    | `proxy.ts` matcher correct; session guard at layout for workspace routes; `sanitizeReturnToPath` on `returnTo`; parameterized queries only |
| **Integration** | `tsc --noEmit` clean; relevant unit test passes; `npm run checks` passes; no half-stack residue                                            |
